Comment: 0,0:00:04.38,0:00:05.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}中文字幕\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}英文字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.38,0:00:05.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你好 我是Scott Manley\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Hello, it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.32,0:00:10.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}几星期前 我谈到了SpaceX已经砍掉的火箭设计\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}A couple of weeks ago I talked about SpaceX has abandoned rocket designs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:15.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}本周 我想谈谈其他技术 也就是SpaceX已经宣传过 然后砍掉的那种\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This week I want to talk about other technologies which SpaceX have pitched and then abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:18.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不一定是火箭整体的设计\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Concepts that weren't entire vehicle designs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:22.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但仍是计划中的东西 可能会被纳入一个完整的运载火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but plans for things that might have been incorporated into a full up launch vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:27.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但最终这些计划都没有看到曙光 或者已经被更好的东西所取代\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But ultimately never saw the light of day or have been replaced with something better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.45,0:00:32.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 SpaceX以其回收助推器(一级火箭)并重复使用的能力而闻名\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}SpaceX are of course known for their ability to recover their boosters and reuse them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:35.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而虽然我们直到2016年才看到着陆\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and while we didn't see a landing until 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:39.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个概念从公司成立之初就一直伴随着他们\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The concept has always been with them from the earliest days of the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.23,0:00:44.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但助推器一开始的计划并不是以那种华丽的悬停猛击动作着陆\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But instead of landing the rocket boosters in that magnificent hover slam maneuver,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.61,0:00:47.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而是使用降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the original plan was to use parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.69,0:00:51.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第一个提出用降落伞回收火箭级的并不是SpaceX\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}They weren't the first to suggest recovering rocket stages with parachutes by any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.04,0:00:55.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}即使是早期的红石火箭 也就是那个用来发射第一个水星飞船的火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Even the early Redstone rocket used to launch the first Mercury capsules
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:00:58.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}设计时就在返回舱下面留有放置降落伞的空间\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}were designed with room for parachutes under the capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:03.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但当然 在这之后使用降落伞进行回收就被美国(各种)航天计划放弃了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But of course the parachute recovery has been abandoned by the US space program
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.64,0:01:05.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}直到航天飞机计划出现\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}until the Space Shuttle program came along
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.19,0:01:09.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}航天飞机回收并翻新了固体火箭助推器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which recovered and refurbished the solid rocket boosters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.10,0:01:15.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么当SpaceX公司在考虑开发低成本火箭时 重复使用就是他们计划的核心部分\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So when SpaceX was looking at developing a low-cost rocket, reuse was a core part of their plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.76,0:01:20.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而早期的猎鹰1号飞行中 包含了Irvin降落伞公司制造的降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And the early Falcon 1 flights included parachutes built by Irvin Parachute Corporation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.93,0:01:23.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}该公司还制造了航天飞机助推器回收系统\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}who also built the Shuttle booster recovery system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.34,0:01:29.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎鹰1号上的回收伞在级间段内 在第一级的顶部\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The recovery parachute on the Falcon 1 was inside the interstage, at the top of the first stage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.43,0:01:34.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而实际上它占据的空间会延伸到二级红隼发动机的发动机喷管中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and it would actually extend up inside the engine Bell of the second stage Kestrel engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.82,0:01:38.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当助推器下降时 其降落伞将在约4公里的高度进行部署\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}When descending it would deploy as an altitude of about four kilometers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.51,0:01:42.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并在理论上让助推器进行在水中的软着陆\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and in theory delivered the booster to a soft touchdown and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.80,0:01:47.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第一次猎鹰1号发射在一二级分离前失败了 所以降落伞没有进行测试\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The first Falcon 1 launch failed before the stage separation so the chute wasn't tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:50.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但第二次发射成功进行了一二级分离\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But the second launch did deploy the second stage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:54.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在助推器消失在地平线之前 发射场对其进行了追踪\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the booster was tracked from the launch site before it disappeared below the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:59.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}回收船在几小时后到达了预定的着陆区\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Our recovery ship reached the predicted landing area a few hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.88,0:02:03.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它并没有找到助推器 也没有收到助推器天线发射的任何信号\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But it didn't find the booster or receive any pings from its beacons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.95,0:02:09.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第四次猎鹰1号飞行的数据显示 助推器很可能在再入过程中被摧毁\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Data from the fourth Falcon 1 flight showed that the booster had probably been destroyed during reentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.61,0:02:15.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在有机会部署降落伞之前 助推器需要升级才能在再入过程中存活下来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And they would need upgrades to survive the descent before it had any chance to deploy parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:20.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎鹰9号的前两次飞行也在级间段加入了降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The first two flights of Falcon 9 also included parachutes in the interstage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:23.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但助推器在再入过程中也解体了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but the boosters also broke up during descent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.41,0:02:27.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}于是这就结束了SpaceX的用降落伞回收助推器的计划\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and that was the end of SpaceX s plans to recover boosters with parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.43,0:02:34.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好吧 所以下一个被抛弃的概念 我想谈的是梅林2 这是一个更大的版本的梅林发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Okay so next abandoned concept I want to talk about is the Merlin 2 which is a larger version of the Merlin engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.13,0:02:41.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX会用单台梅林2号发动机取代猎鹰9号一级的所有9台梅林发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And they would replace all nine Merlin engines in the first stage of a Falcon 9 with his single Merlin 2
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:44.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}推力甚至还要再多一些\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and it would actually have more thrust on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.96,0:02:49.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 发动机的循环和喷注器的设计并没有任何真正的改变\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Now there weren't any real changes to the engine cycle or the injector design.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:51.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它实际上只是梅林的放大版\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It was really just a scaled up version of the Merlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:57.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一台梅林2号发动机可以产生高达750吨的推力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And a single Merlin 2 engine would develop a thrust of up to 750 tons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.49,0:03:02.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这实际上会使它与驱动土星5号的F1发动机非常相似\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which would actually make it very similar to the F1 engine that powered the Saturn 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:09.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以在2010年的联合推进会议上 梅林2号的设计细节出现在了演讲中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So details of the design of the Merlin 2 came up in a presentation in 2010 at the joint propulsion conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.58,0:03:15.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而论文的重点虽然是简单地用简化版取代现有的猎鹰9号\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and while the paper focused on simply replacing the existing Falcon 9 with a simplified version,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.44,0:03:20.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们也在研究建造更大更好的火箭 以充分利用梅林2号的能力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}they also looked at building bigger and better rockets that could exploit the power of the Merlin 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.11,0:03:26.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}于是就有了猎鹰X号 它将推进剂储罐的直径扩大到6米\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So there was the Falcon X and this would scale up the propellant tanks to 6 meter diameter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.83,0:03:33.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}并能安装3台梅林2号发动机 拥有差不多38吨的近地轨道运载能力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and allow 3 Merlin 2 engines with the ability to throw a bit 38 tons into low-earth orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.41,0:03:38.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}当然还有用3个这样的助推器芯级捆绑而成的猎鹰X重型火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And of course there was the Falcon X Heavy made of three of these booster cores bolted together
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:41.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}并可携带高达125吨的有效载荷\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and that would carry payloads of up to 125 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.62,0:03:45.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}但还有一款猎鹰XX\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But then there was a Falcon XX.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:53.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}一枚10米宽的助推器 百米高 配备6台梅林2号发动机 能够将140吨的载荷送入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}A 10 meter wide booster, a hundred metres tall with six Merlin two engines and able to throw 140 tons into orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.31,0:03:59.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}而这样一来 它的体积和近地轨道有效载荷质量就和Starship差不多了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And this would put it in the same ballpark as Starship in terms of size and low Earth orbit payload.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:03.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}但并没有Starship计划中的完全可重复使用性\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but without the full reusability planned for Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.67,0:04:08.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\a6}而这部分原因是梅林2比猛禽效率较低\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and this is partly because the Merlin 2 has lower efficiency compared to the Raptors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:16.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上猎鹰9号上的9个小发动机是其能够进行助推器降落的重要原因\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The thing is having nine small engines on the Falcon 9 is a big part of why is able to perform the booster landings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.89,0:04:21.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当助推器几乎是空的时候 只需要相当于发射时推力的5%这么小的程度就可以悬停了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}When the booster is almost empty only needs a bit 5% of its launch thrust to hover
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:29.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以能够只使用九个引擎中的一个 是能够控制下降过程的一个巨大优势\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and so being able to use just one of the nine engines is a huge advantage in being able to control the descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.43,0:04:32.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这一点直到很多年后才被真正意识到\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And that wasn't really appreciated until many years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:36.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我们并没有听到更多关于梅林2号的消息\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And so we didn't really hear more about the Merlin 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:41.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且它消失了 与此同时猛禽成为了SpaceX的下一代发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Instead it disappeared and Raptor became SpaceX's next generation engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.53,0:04:44.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与梅林2相比 猛禽是一款更为复杂的设备\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}a much more complicated device compared to the Merlin 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.31,0:04:49.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但其实猛禽早于梅林2 在2009年就出现了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But the Raptor actually appeared before the Merlin 2 in 2009.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.76,0:04:53.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不过当时它是一款闭式循环氢氧发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Back then however it was a closed cycle hydrogen-oxygen engine
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.61,0:04:56.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}作为猎鹰9号的二级发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}that was being pitched as a second stage engine for the Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:02.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其推力可与梅林媲美 但很明显 其比冲比梅林号高很多\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And it would have a thrust comparable to the Merlin but obviously a specific impulse was much much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:06.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这一概念 当然 在2012年被放弃\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But that concept, of course was abandoned in 2012.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:12.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猛禽目前的形式是燃烧甲烷的高推力一级发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Raptor for current form as a high thrust first stage engine burning methane
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.35,0:05:14.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并采用全流量分级燃烧循环\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and using a full flow staged combustion cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.53,0:05:19.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 在这些年里 它的尺寸 推力和性能都发生了一些变化\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Now it's changed a bit over the years in terms of size thrust and performance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:23.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但目前是SpaceX公司未来的发动机 而且是可以追溯到2012年的型号\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but is currently the future engine of SpaceX and it dates back to the 2012 model.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.79,0:05:27.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但猛禽发动机有一个被放弃的概念\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But there is one abandoned concept for the Raptor engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.90,0:05:33.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2016年 美国空军授予SpaceX公司一份开发猛禽的合同\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}In 2016 the US Air Force awarded SpaceX a contract to develop Raptor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:38.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}让其作为猎鹰9号更高效的二级发动机 取代目前的二级发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}as a higher efficiency second stage engine for the Falcon 9 replacing the current second stage
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.27,0:05:41.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这将有助于一些任务概况的制定\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and this would help with some mission profiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:47.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而SpaceX公司已经研究并利用这一点来开发猛禽 并进行了纸面的提案\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And while SpaceX has worked on and used that to develop the Raptor and come up with proposals on paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:51.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这个概念还没有被开发成一个实际工作的上面级\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the concept hasn't been developed into an actual working upper stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好了 不说发动机了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Okay so enough about the engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:57.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当载人龙飞船首次亮相时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Back when Crew Dragon was first revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.17,0:06:01.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX希望它能在着陆点进行精确的反推式着陆\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}SpaceX wanted it to perform a precision propulsive touchdown at a landing site
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.85,0:06:05.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}使用超级天龙座推进器 而不是使用降落伞和海上溅落\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}using the Super Draco thrusters instead of using parachutes and a splashdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.81,0:06:13.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然也有很多人怀疑这是否能通过NASA的风险规避型安全审查\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And there were certainly many who were skeptical this would ever make it past NASA's risk-averse safety reviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.53,0:06:16.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不过 SpaceX有着充分的技术理由来调查反推式着陆\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But there were good technical reasons to investigate the propulsive landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:19.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与其他载人航天器不同的是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Unlike other human-rated spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:23.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}载人龙飞船的超级天龙座发射逃逸发动机是内置在飞船里的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Crew Dragons Super Draco launch escape thrusters are built into the capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:28.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}逃逸所使用的推进剂\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The propellant supply needed for it for the abort is the same
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:32.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与在太空中操纵的较小的天龙座发动机所使用的燃料是相同的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which is also used for the smaller Draco thrusters used for maneuvering in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.27,0:06:37.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些设备 用于火箭发射失败时的逃逸的同时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The same hardware that is needed to push the capsule free from a fallen rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.40,0:06:40.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也需要用来将飞船着陆在着陆场上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}has the ability to bring the capsule stop at a landing pad
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:44.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在逃逸时 (因为逃逸会消耗反推式着陆时的燃料 所以)不管怎样还是需要降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and parachutes are required either way for the abort scenario
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:48.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以如果在反推式着陆过程中出现问题 也可以使用降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}so those would be available if there was a problem during a propulsive landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.67,0:06:51.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在飞船需要一些额外的硬件\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Now the capsule would need some extra hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:54.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它需要一些用于控制着陆的传感器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It would need some sensors for controlling the touchdown
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:57.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 它也需要一套起落架\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and of course it would need a set of landing legs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:07:01.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在视觉上 它将穿过隔热板\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which in the visualizations would extend through the heat shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.68,0:07:07.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 任何侵入隔热板的行为 都会让NASA的安全人员有点紧张\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And of course any intrusion through the heat shield does make the safety people at NASA a little edgy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.70,0:07:11.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但事实是 并不是安全问题终结了这个概念\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but the truth is it wasn't safety concerns that really killed this as a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:15.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而是时间 时间是最重要的资源\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It was more the time was the most important resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:17.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无论如何 他们都需要有一个降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}They needed to have a parachute either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.57,0:07:21.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这是一个很容易的争论 那就是SpaceX可以放弃反推式着陆 而只是使用降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And it was an easy argument that they could drop propulsive landing and just use those parachutes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至降落伞的部署\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and even the parachute deployment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.27,0:07:27.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也是载人龙飞船研发过程中比较麻烦的一件事\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}was one of the more troubling things during the development of Crew Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:34.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX刚在2019年年底(才)公开记录其降落伞测试的成功率\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}SpaceX were publicly documenting its success rate of the parachute test just at the end of 2019
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.13,0:07:40.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以反推式着陆技术也是红龙飞船概念的核心\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So the propulsive landing technology was also core to the concept of Red Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:43.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是SpaceX提出的火星任务\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}SpaceX proposed a Mars mission
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:48.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是运送一个实验性的有效载荷到火星上 以及一个改装过的龙飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}where an experimental payload would be transported to Mars and a modified Dragon capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:07:53.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}红龙飞船将用重型猎鹰发射到火星转移轨道上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Red Dragon would be launched onto the Mars transfer trajectory on a Falcon Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.56,0:07:55.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而着陆将主要依赖红龙飞船\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And landing would be heavily dependent on Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.96,0:07:59.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}通过其空气动力学(特性)来尽可能地减少速度\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}using his aerodynamics to bleed off as much speed as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.13,0:08:03.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时保持升力 然后用超级天龙座进行降落\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}while maintaining lift and then performing the landing using with Super Dracos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:09.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与其他火星航天器不同的是 降落过程中不会涉及降落伞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Unlike other Martian spacecraft, no parachutes would have been involved in the landing process.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.22,0:08:15.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}红龙飞船最初是在2011年作为可能的低成本NASA发现任务提出的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Red Dragon was originally proposed as a potential low cost NASA discovery mission in 2011.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:18.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}该提议包括一个钻探实验\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The proposal included a drilling experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.94,0:08:23.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和一个可以进行提取水和生产推进剂的实验\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and an experiment which would perform water extraction and propellant production.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然而它未能获得该计划的进一步资助\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}However it failed to get further funding from the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.88,0:08:29.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但SpaceX继续开发这个概念\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But SpaceX continued to develop the concept
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:35.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}直到2017年 马一龙宣布停止该项目 改用Starship\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}until 2017 when Elon announced that the project was being discontinued in favor of Starship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:38.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 虽然当时还不叫Starship\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Although at the time of course it wasn't known as Starship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.55,0:08:41.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它被称为ITS或BFR\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It was known as the ITS or the BFR.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:44.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但无论如何 我认为今天这期节目最好到此为止\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But either way I think this is a good place to leave off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:48.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们还有一整集的废弃项目要谈\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}We have a whole other episode of abandoned projects to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.55,0:08:50.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那之前 我是Scott Manley\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Until then I'm Scott Manley.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:51.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}切记 注意飞行安全\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Fly safe.
